# Trivy CVE ignore list. Every entry MUST cite a reason and a re-evaluation
# trigger. Untriaged findings should not live here.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line; comments start with '#'.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vendored copies inside next/dist/compiled/
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Next.js ships pre-compiled, dependency-flat copies of these utilities under
# next/dist/compiled/<package>/ so user projects don't get conflicting
# versions. Trivy fingerprints the vendored bundles as the upstream package
# at its pre-compile version (often 1–2 majors behind upstream) and flags
# their CVEs.
#
# These CVEs are NOT reachable from the StackSift runtime:
#   - The vendored cross-spawn/tar/glob/minimatch sit inside Next's compiled
#     build helpers (next dev, next build, archive extraction during
#     prerendering). The standalone server.js used in production does not
#     execute these code paths.
#   - We never extract user-supplied tarballs, never spawn user-controlled
#     processes, never glob user-controlled patterns.
#
# Re-evaluation trigger: bump to a Next.js version whose dist/compiled/ has
# refreshed bundles. Track at https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues
# (search "trivy" or the specific CVE id). Re-run `trivy image` after every
# next.js bump and remove entries that no longer report.
#
# Reviewed: 2026-05-29 against next@16.2.6.

CVE-2024-21538  # cross-spawn ReDoS — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2025-64756  # glob path traversal — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-26996  # minimatch ReDoS — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-27903  # minimatch ReDoS — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-27904  # minimatch ReDoS — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-23745  # tar arbitrary file overwrite — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-23950  # tar Unicode path collision — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-24842  # tar hardlink bypass — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-26960  # tar arbitrary read/write via hardlink — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-29786  # tar drive-relative linkpath — vendored, unused at runtime
CVE-2026-31802  # tar drive-relative symlink overwrite — vendored, unused at runtime

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Go stdlib in /usr/local/bin/gosu (stacksift-postgres image)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# gosu is the standard tianon/gosu privilege-drop helper baked into the
# upstream postgres image (used by /usr/local/bin/docker-entrypoint.sh to
# drop from root to the postgres user before exec'ing postgres). It is a
# ~150-LOC Go program whose only system calls are setgroups/setgid/setuid
# and exec — see https://github.com/tianon/gosu.
#
# Trivy fingerprints the Go stdlib version it was built against (currently
# v1.24.6) and flags every Go stdlib CVE for that version. None of the
# flagged CVEs are reachable from gosu:
#   - gosu never opens a network socket → all crypto/tls, crypto/x509,
#     net/http, net/url, net/textproto findings are unreachable.
#   - gosu never reads a tar archive → tar.Reader findings are unreachable.
#   - gosu never parses HTTP/2 → http2 SETTINGS findings are unreachable.
# The Trivy report itself notes "Fixed Version" entries — the upstream
# gosu maintainers ship Go-version bumps in their own cadence; we pick the
# next one up at the next pgvector/pgvector:pg16 base-image refresh.
#
# Re-evaluation trigger: pgvector/pgvector:pg16 publishes a newer image
# whose bundled /usr/local/bin/gosu links a Go stdlib version past 1.25.10.
# Track at https://github.com/tianon/gosu/releases. Re-run trivy after
# every postgres-image rebuild and remove entries that no longer report.
#
# Reviewed: 2026-05-29 against pgvector/pgvector:pg16 (gosu Go v1.24.6).

CVE-2025-47912  # gosu/Go stdlib net/url IPv6 parse — unreachable
CVE-2025-58183  # gosu/Go stdlib tar.Reader size limit — unreachable
CVE-2025-58185  # gosu/Go stdlib DER allocation — unreachable
CVE-2025-58186  # gosu/Go stdlib HTTP header limit — unreachable
CVE-2025-58187  # gosu/Go stdlib name constraints — unreachable
CVE-2025-58188  # gosu/Go stdlib DSA cert validation — unreachable
CVE-2025-58189  # gosu/Go stdlib ALPN error — unreachable
CVE-2025-61723  # gosu/Go stdlib parse scaling — unreachable
CVE-2025-61724  # gosu/Go stdlib Reader.ReadResponse — unreachable
CVE-2025-61725  # gosu/Go stdlib ParseAddress — unreachable
CVE-2025-61726  # gosu/Go stdlib net/url memory — unreachable
CVE-2025-61727  # gosu/Go stdlib subdomain constraint — unreachable
CVE-2025-61729  # gosu/Go stdlib HostnameError — unreachable
CVE-2025-68121  # gosu/Go stdlib crypto/tls cert validation — unreachable (no TLS in gosu)
CVE-2026-25679  # gosu/Go stdlib net/url IPv6 — unreachable
